cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper deals with a machine learning algorithm for imitation learning, which involves mapping actions between a teacher and a learner having substantially different embodiments. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category, as the paper presents a general, model-free, and non-parametric imitation learning algorithm based on regression between two Hilbert spaces. The other categories are also likely, as the paper applies the algorithm to a static posture imitation task between two robotic manipulators with different embodiments, and analyzes its statistical and computational aspects.
